===Etymology===
From the Proto-Indo-European root ''*deru- / *dreu-'' (''firm, solid, steadfast''); cf. [[trú]].

===Noun===
'''drūwis'''
# [[belief]], [[faith]], [[religion]]

===Usage notes===
The word is customarily begun with a majuscule letter (''see [[Drūwis]]'') in the formal names of religions, out of respect, although this rule is by no means binding : ''[[jūdiskas|Jūdiskas]] [[Drūwis]]'' - "''the [[Jewish]] [[faith|Faith]]''"; ''[[krikstāniskas|Krikstāniskas]] [[Drūwis]]'' - "''the [[Christian]] [[faith|Faith]]''".

